Bill of Material (Items needed)
Wemos Mini D1 (V3.0.0)
Raspberry Pi3 (9.9 Stretch Version)
Windows 10 (for Arduino configuration)
1 Micro-USB to USB Cable

Step1: Perform the following in RaspberryPi3 under root user.
 sudo apt-get update
 sudo apt-get upgrade
 sudo apt-get install mosquitto -y
 sudo apt-get install mosquitto-clients y
Finally perform MQTT testing between Server and Client within RPi3 itself

Step2: 
Connect the Mirco USB end to Wemos and USB end to the Windows 10 Machine.
Ensure the in-built Blue LED light flickers when it is powered by the USB cable.
Using Device Manager > Ports verify whether it is visible as Port 4
Switch off the Antiwirus and Firewall
Install Arduino IDE
Under Preferences update the location as
As on 10-MAY-2019, select the Board as LOLIN(WEMOS) D1 R1 & mini under ESP8266 Boards 
Run the sample sketch 'Blink'
